_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Bivariate function data objects are functions of two arguments,
     $f(s,t)$.  It can be useful to evaluate the function for argument
     values satisying $s=t$, such as evaluating the univariate variance
     function given the bivariate function that defines the
     variance-covariance function or surface.  A linear differential
     operator can be applied to function $f(s,t)$ considered as a
     univariate function of either object holding the other object
     fixed.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     evaldiag.bifd(evalarg, bifdobj, sLfd=int2Lfd(0),
                                     tLfd=int2Lfd(0))

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

 evalarg: a vector of values of $s = t$. 

 bifdobj: a bivariate functional data object of the 'bifd' class. 

    sLfd: either a nonnegative integer or a linear differential
          operator object. 

    tLfd: either a nonnegative integer or a linear differential
          operator object. 

